Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, with gradual curve. Clay near fine orange-buff. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie noted several such stamps in his 1884-5 diary (EES Archive XVII 47) Name Ageloch(os).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0385)
